cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper discusses techniques to improve the viewer experience of stereoscopic 3D displays, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed techniques involve manipulating the optics of the display, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper mentions conducting performance tests, which could relate to robotics (cs.RO) if the tests involved robots.
